{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revise firearms certificates to allow for wider gun access but harder to obtain",
        "additional_details": "The revisions I am proposing are:\r\nAllow for the sale of semi-automatic, centre-fire rifles to citizens with a section 1 firearms certificate\r\nAllow for the sale of pistols to citizens with a section 1 firearms certificate\r\nAllow for the protection of private property to be a reason for owning a firearm\r\nReduce the length of firearm certificate to be reduce from 5 to 1 year so mental health and criminal checks happen more often\r\nChange the price of a certificate to make renewal easy but entry hard",
        "background": "We want to see revisions to Section 1 firearms certificates so that law abiding, mentally healthy citizens have the privilege and freedom to own a wider range of weaponry for the purposes of sports and protection of private property.",
